callgraph
Class CallGraph

java.lang.Object
  callgraph.CallGraph
public class CallGraph
extends java.lang.Object

A reusable class for generating a call graph based on JGraph. A typical usage of the class is quite simple: (1) creating a new instance of CallGraph; (2) add procedures and call sites to the call graph instance; (3) add procedure calls to the call graph instance; (4) show the call graph. The following is a demonstrative usage: 

		...
		CallGraph graph = new CallGraph();
		// Add procedure nodes
		graph.addProcedure("sub", "expr");
		graph.addProcedure("main", "program");
		// Add call sites
		graph.addCallSite("c1", "program", "e = expr();");
		// Add procedure calls
		graph.addEdge("main", "sub");
		// Show the graph
		graph.show();
Note that the procedures and call sites may be added to the graph in any order, but a procedure call must be added only after the source call site and the target procedure have been added to the graph, otherwise a SourceNotFoundException or a TargetNotFoundException will be raised.

Version:
1.01 (Last update: June 4, 2008)
Author:
